result.name: FRITES Belgium on Tap

reviews.text: The Wanchai location has a very relaxing ambience with an alfresco dining option. They recently introduced an unlimited steak and fries deal, which I opted for. The chimichurri sauce was the perfect complement to my steak. Fox was also very helpful and friendly. Overall a nice dining experience.

Personally, as a Bangkok dweller, I consider this place to be one of my mandatory stops every time I’m in Hong Kong. Why? The food is very nice, it tastes like home (northern part of France) and the beer bible is epic! I’d love them to open a venue on Silom Road in Bangkok too 😋
Great place for socialising. No distracting sports Tv's to mar a conversation. Menu was quite varied. Mid- high price levels $$-$$$
Awesome Belgic beers and staff. Half price happy hour. Good food choice. Great atmosphere.

Very crowded at lunch time. Services are good but you'll need to check the orders because they've missed a couple of ours. Good food but small portions. No view / relaxing area, it is all packed and crazy.
